# E2E Testing with Playwright

This project uses [Playwright](https://playwright.dev/) for End-to-End tests. Never use Vitest or React Testing Library for E2E — use Playwright only. Vitest is reserved for unit tests on synchronous components.

## When to Write E2E Tests

- `async` Server Components (cannot be unit tested with Vitest)
- Full user flows (auth, navigation, CRUD operations)
- Features that span multiple pages or server/client boundaries

## File Location

Place all E2E tests in the `tests/` directory at the project root:

```
tests/
  example.spec.ts
  decks.spec.ts
```

Test files must end in `.spec.ts`.

## Running Tests

Tests must run against the production build:

```bash
pnpm build && pnpm start
# in another terminal:
npx playwright test
```

## Writing Tests

```ts
// ✅ GOOD — use baseURL from playwright.config.ts
import { test, expect } from '@playwright/test'

test('should navigate to the about page', async ({ page }) => {
  await page.goto('/')
  await page.click('text=About')
  await expect(page).toHaveURL('/about')
  await expect(page.locator('h1')).toContainText('About')
})

// ❌ BAD — hardcoded full URLs
await page.goto('http://localhost:3000/about')
```

## Config Requirements

`playwright.config.ts` must set `baseURL`:

```ts
use: {
  baseURL: 'http://localhost:3000',
},
```

## Rules

- All E2E tests live in `tests/` and use `.spec.ts` extension
- Always use `baseURL`-relative paths (`'/'` not `'http://localhost:3000/'`)
- Run against the production build (`pnpm build && pnpm start`), not the dev server
- Use `async` Server Component flows as the primary motivation for E2E tests
- Never duplicate E2E tests for logic already covered by Vitest unit tests
